About OnLoad

OnLoad is a weekend-long spectacle aimed at bringing together young talented programmers, designers, and developers from across the country to collaborate to build innovative projects from scratch.

36 hours

36 hours time span covering exhilarating sessions of coding, talks, workshops make OnLoad a must attend event.

Talks

It will be an unprecedented congregation of renowned speakers.

Workshops

Discover how the latest technologies are implemented.

Networking

An excellent opportunity for you to build professional contacts and make new friends.

Why should I attend??

To Learn

OnLoad is the platform that offers an excellent opportunity for you to interact and build connections with professionals and helps you meet like-minded individuals. With over 150 developers and designers gathering from all over the country, grab your chance of connecting with people to discuss ideas and opportunities.

To Build

Programming abecedarians get to create projects from scratch, buff out the problems and present to a panel of judges. Individuals who are pros at coding have an opportunity to hone their team collaboration and presentation skills.

To Network

Hackathons provide an excellent opportunity for you to build professional contacts and make new friends. With over 300 developers and designers gathering from all over the country, grab your chance of connecting with people to discuss ideas and opportunities.

The Thrill

If you haven’t hacked a Hackathon you can’t know the feeling you have. The agitation before. Will you be able to finish something? And the excitement afterward, when you are finished and you have created something. A Hackathon is a challenge that comes with a lot of work, but also a lot of fun and it can be an experience of a lifetime.

To Flaunt Your Skills

Participating in hackathons will help you stand out from the competition and, show that you truly are passionate about coding. Hackathon projects can also be great additions to your portfolio. They can lead to great product creations, which make them a unique opportunity to get in front of industry leaders to showcase your technical skills.

To win Prizes and cool Schwags

Not only will you have the chance to win some cool stuff, but you will also get a cool goodie bag and loads of schwags. And food and drinks will also be for free. Overall it is an event full of rewards.

Frequently Asked Questions

Who can participate?

Everyone. Yes, everyone. If you are under 18 years of age, we’ll need a parental consent form.

How does the application process work?

We’re looking for people who 'do'! Folks who are passionate enough to work on crazy world-changing ideas. Tell us what makes you apply to OnLoad, what excites you, accomplishments you are proud of and whatever else you think can strengthen your chances of acceptance. We’ll get to know more about your abilities from the past projects, GitHub profile, participation/awards in other hackathons.

Can we apply as a team?

Yes! This hackathon is strictly a team competition. We believe that you’re stronger as a team than you are apart. You can join or create a team once you've started an individual application.

What if i don't have a team or an idea?

Not to worry, most people don’t! We’ll have team formation and ideation events geared towards helping you find people to work with.

What shouldn't I bring?

Weapons of any kind, drugs, or alcohol. If you’re not sure whether something will be okay, please ask ahead of time!

What about Hardware?

If you need any hardware mail or tweet us about it. We will try our best to arrange all your hardware needs.

I don't want to hack, but i still get involved?

If you're looking to be a volunteer or mentor (i.e. someone with technical skills who'd be willing to help out participants during the weekend), you should reach out to us at volunteer@hackonload.com. If your company is interested in becoming a sponsor, write to us at sponsor@hackonload.com

When will application close?

The application portal will be closed on 10th Feb, 2020 at 11:59pm IST. We evaluate applications on a rolling basis and acceptances will be sent every weekend via email. The sooner you apply, the better chances you have of acceptance. Once accepted, you’ll have two days to confirm your attendance

How much does it cost?

Zero. Zip. Zilch. Nada. Nothing. Admission to OnLoad is completely free, thanks to our sponsors! We'll provide you with a weekend's worth of schwags, meals, drinks, snacks and a place to crash when you need a break from coding.

How big a team can be?

You can form teams of up to 3 people. Most teams aim to have a mix of people with both design and developer skills.

Once i am accepted, what do i need to bring?

A valid government/college issued photo ID, laptop, phone, chargers, any sleeping equipment you might want (we'll be providing mattresses)

Do you provide travel reimbursement

No, we won't be able to provide reimbursements.

What do you get by attending OnLoad?

Pretty much everything from socializing with fellow hacker community to internship/job offers from the coolest tech companies. And yeah we’ll have prizes for finalist teams, and many other company sponsored prizes. Most of all, you will gain an unparalleled learning experience and memories for a lifetime!

How does judging work?

A panel of some of the judges will evaluate hacks based on creativity, technical difficulty, design, and usefulness. The top 7 overall projects will demo what they have built in front of everyone.

How to reach VVCE, Mysuru?

Mysore is just 3hr journey from Bengaluru by train/bus. We will send you a detailed guide once you are accepted.

Can I start working on the project before the event?

No. In the interest of fairness, students should not be working on their projects before OnLoad begins and we do not allow participants to work on pre-existing projects. However, you can start thinking of ideas and familiarize yourself with all the tools and technologies you intend to use beforehand!
